    "summary": "The Frontier Mountains are the highest and roughest set of mountians located on the continent. These harsh mountains cut across the western half of the continent, and are inhabited by a variety of powerful, large creatures, for whom the peaks are mere hills. Many of these creatures operate vast mining operations in the mountains for the minerals that lie beneath them. Note: Due to post-classic revamps of Droga and Nurga, many mobs (mainly goblins) were moved to FM on live. On P99 **prior to the Chardok 2.0 patch** all these goblins should reside in their original zones, not in FM. However, as of 2/10/2019 that patch has been added to P99. This will complicate this page a bit. TODO: Create two copies of this page, Frontier Mountains (Pre-Revamp) and Frontier Mountains (Post-Revamp). Change this page to just be a link to each one, with a brief explanation of why there's two pages. Then on each page remove all content from the previous/post era, so that each page only contains era-correct details.",
