//giantbomb1.cbsistatic.com/uploads/original/1/14259/470050-eq015.sized.jpg (low level group hanging around in the spiky pit room outside the Phido area) http://web.archive.org/web/20001028013847if_/http://members.home.net:80/lore1/images/gnoll_splitpaw.jpg (splitpaw gnoll in one of the bedrooms near the entrance) https://github.com/dbsanfte/eq-archives/blob/master/screenshots/classic_paw/E5Uk8Lf.png (Kurrpok Splitpaw) https://github.com/dbsanfte/eq-archives/blob/master/screenshots/classic_paw/FEgxkFC.png (High Shaman Phido with aggro message) https://github.com/dbsanfte/eq-archives/blob/master/screenshots/classic_paw/NlH9NyQ.png (Zixx Nenix in fight with spell) https://github.com/dbsanfte/eq-archives/blob/master/screenshots/classic_paw/ZeSJgc1.png (Ghanex the Resurrected fight) https://github.com/dbsanfte/eq-archives/blob/master/screenshots/classic_paw/hkaQtUA.png (High shaman Grisok in his room) https://github.com/dbsanfte/eq-archives/blob/master/screenshots/classic_paw/p9J14bh.png (High Shaman Phido in his room, and bat death) https://github.com/dbsanfte/eq-archives/blob/master/screenshots/classic_paw/sMW0Meo.png (Zixx Nenix in fight with spell) https://github.com/dbsanfte/eq-archives/blob/master/screenshots/classic_paw/vJoTef2.png (Ghanex the Resurrected with aggro message) https://github.com/dbsanfte/eq-archives/blob/master/screenshots/classic_paw/uoimySv.png (Zixx Nenix death message and faction hits) https://arcanekindred.fortunecity.ws/kindred1.jpg (Low level group killing some nobles) == All Known Classic Maps of Infected Paw == There are two versions. One is based on the original Hop map with original spawn points (thank God we have this). The second is a very incomplete Everlore map that I trust a lot less. https://www.steveprutz.com/eq/images/splitpaw_hop.gif https://www.steveprutz.com/eq/images/splitpaw_hop_invectus.jpg https://www.steveprutz.com/eq/images/splitpaw_hop_lifebane.jpg http://web.archive.org/web/20150321173739/https://www.steveprutz.com/eq/everlore/splitpaw_everlore.jpg Edit: I have found another version, by the Japanese Questor of Norrath guy, which I believe is very accurate: https://web.archive.org/web/20210610124225/https://metabrain.tripod.com/ant_map/InfectedPaw.jpg == Full Spawn Dump of Infected Paw == I was able to locate a full spawn dump of the zone from late 1999, with mob counts. These line up very well, although not quite exactly, with the spawns on Hop's map. Most notably, it would seem the front area before the double doors had lower level gnolls, but the map doesn't make this distinction. Note that the Count is zero-based, like the EQ mob names. A 0 means there was 1 instance of the mob in the zone, ie a_large_snake00. https://www.project1999.com/forums/showpost.php?p=3073391&postcount=2",
